headline.main: Prevention of Illness Is Aim of New Computerized Testing Here

docs.abstract: HIP opens computerized testing center to check people for over 50 possible abnormalities without their being touched by drs; testing procedure described; illus
docs.lead_paragraph: The Health Insurance Plan of Greater New York yesterday opened a computerized testing center that will check people for more than 50 possible medical abnormalities without their being touched by a physician.
